definitions.definition: Any one of numerous edible, marine, spiny-finned fishes of the family Labridae , of which several species are found in the Mediterranean and on the Atlantic coast of Europe. Many of the species are brightly colored.

main_definition: Any one of numerous edible, marine, spiny-finned fishes of the family Labridae , of which several species are found in the Mediterranean and on the Atlantic coast of Europe. Many of the species are brightly colored. [from mid-17th c.]
